{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Traditional regulatory approaches make it effectively impossible to have compliant real-time or near-real-time adaptive/continuous learning AI-enabled medical devices.",
    "Innovative/agile proposals: The FDA has proposed an approach for on-market adaptive AI 90 through Predetermined Change Control Plans (PCCPs) and have introduced some of these proposals in recent guidance 39, 89, 97, 111.",
    "This approach allows the developer to specify a threshold/envelope of allowed changes in the AI-model, including in its performance, for which a new approval/clearance process would not be required 131.",
    "Our perspective: The FDA's guidance for PCCPs falls short of the ambition of its initial description of a framework for on-market adaptive AI-models, as changed models must be brought through standard design control processes of design justification and verification.",
    "This effectively precludes on-market adaptivity 131."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
